                <r3d:description language="eng">The Tromsø Repository of Language and Linguistics (TROLLing) is a FAIR-aligned repository of linguistic data and statistical code. The archive is open access, which means that all information is available to everyone. All data are accompanied by searchable metadata that identify the researchers, the languages and linguistic phenomena involved, the statistical methods applied, and scholarly publications based on the data (where relevant). Linguists worldwide are invited to deposit data and statistical code used in their linguistic research.

TROLLing is a special collection within DataverseNO (http://doi.org/10.17616/R3TV17), and C Centre within CLARIN (Common Language Resources and Technology Infrastructure, a networked federation of European data repositories; http://www.clarin.eu/), and harvested by their Virtual Language Observatory (VLO; https://vlo.clarin.eu/).</r3d:description>
